<chapter>
  <title>Cash Management</title>

  <info />

  <para role="TEXT">This chapter helps you to manage your cash transactions for foreign
  exchanges, term deposits, and foreign exchange orders using Opics
  Portal.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Activity</title>

    <para role="TEXT">Using Opics Portal, you can view all customer and customer group
    level deal activities for supported modules, such as foreign exchange,
    term deposit, and foreign exchange order.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">In the portal <emphasis>Home page</emphasis>, click <emphasis>Cash
    Management </emphasis>and then click <emphasis>Activity</emphasis>.
    Specify the following and click <emphasis>Search</emphasis> to view
    transaction details.</para>

    <informaltable frame="all">
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colname="column-1" colwidth="2668*" />

        <colspec colname="column-2" colwidth="6080*" />

        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry>Field</entry>

            <entry>Description</entry>
          </row>
        </thead>

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
              <para role="TEXT">
                <guilabel>Customer Reference</guilabel>
              </para>
            </entry>

            <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
              <para role="TEXT">Indicates the customer reference number for the
              deal.</para>
            </entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
              <para role="TEXT">
                <guilabel>Customer Group</guilabel>
              </para>
            </entry>

            <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
              <para role="TEXT">Identifies a group that is associated with the
              customer.</para>
            </entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
              <para role="TEXT">
                <guilabel>Start Date</guilabel>
              </para>
            </entry>

            <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
              <para role="TEXT">Select a start date from the pop-up calendar.</para>

              <note>
                <para role="TEXT">: The displayed deals are outstanding from the date
                entered and beyond. Any matured or settled deals as of the
                entered date are not displayed. This field defaults to the
                branch processing date.</para>
              </note>
            </entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </informaltable>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Output</title>

      <para role="TEXT">The result displays basic details of your account as given
      below.</para>

      <informaltable frame="all">
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="column-1" colwidth="2668*" />

          <colspec colname="column-2" colwidth="6080*" />

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Field</entry>

              <entry>Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Deal Number</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Identifies the unique number of the deal.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Deal Date</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays the date the deal or account activity was
                entered.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Value Date</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays the deal value date or the account
                activity.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Currency</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Indicates the currency in which the deal is
                denominated.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Amount</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Identifies the deal amount.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Description</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays details concerning the trade, account movement,
                etc.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Instruction</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays the dealâ€™s instruction status as
                <emphasis>Complete</emphasis> or
                <emphasis>Incomplete</emphasis>.</para>

                <note>
                  <para role="TEXT">: This field appears as
                  <emphasis>Incomplete</emphasis> until instructions are added
                  to both sides of the deal (if applicable) and they have been
                  successfully interfaced.</para>
                </note>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Maturity Date</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Indicates the transaction maturity date or settlement
                date of an FX forward option.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Account Type</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Identifies the call and notice or safekeeping account of
                the deal.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>FX Deals</title>

    <para role="TEXT">In the portal <emphasis>Home page</emphasis>, click <emphasis>Cash
    Management </emphasis>and then click <emphasis>FX Deals</emphasis>. The
    <emphasis>FX Deals</emphasis> section facilitates you to perform inquiries
    on FX Deal Position, Net FX Position by Day, and FX Deal Activity.</para>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Position Summary</title>

      <para role="TEXT">This section displays a list of net FX currency position across
      all dates for each customer or bank.</para>

      <note>
        <para role="TEXT">: The display result depends on your user account
        permissions.</para>
      </note>

      <para role="TEXT">Select the <emphasis>Customer Reference</emphasis>, specify the
      <emphasis>Customer Group</emphasis> and select a <emphasis>Start
      Date</emphasis> from the pop-up calendar and click
      <emphasis>Search</emphasis>.</para>

      <section role="ITEM">
        <title>Output</title>

        <para role="TEXT">The result displays the following details.</para>

        <informaltable frame="all">
          <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec colname="column-1" colwidth="2668*" />

            <colspec colname="column-2" colwidth="6080*" />

            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry>Field</entry>

                <entry>Description</entry>
              </row>
            </thead>

            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <para role="TEXT">
                    <guilabel>Branch</guilabel>
                  </para>
                </entry>

                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <para role="TEXT">Identifies the name of the branch where the customer
                  is an operator and holds an FX position.</para>
                </entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <para role="TEXT">
                    <guilabel>Customer</guilabel>
                  </para>
                </entry>

                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <para role="TEXT">Specifies is the short name of the customer.</para>
                </entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <para role="TEXT">
                    <guilabel>Currency</guilabel>
                  </para>
                </entry>

                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <para role="TEXT">Indicates the currency in which the deal is
                  denominated.</para>
                </entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <para role="TEXT">
                    <guilabel>Amount</guilabel>
                  </para>
                </entry>

                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <para role="TEXT">Identifies the deal amount.</para>
                </entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </informaltable>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Position By Day</title>

      <para role="TEXT">While performing inquiries for the FX position summary for a
      specific currency customer, or bank, the underlying projected FX
      position per day is also displayed.</para>

      <para role="TEXT"><emphasis>Position By Day</emphasis> section displays the
      following details.</para>

      <informaltable frame="all">
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="column-1" colwidth="2668*" />

          <colspec colname="column-2" colwidth="6080*" />

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Field</entry>

              <entry>Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Value Date</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays each date in which a customer has an
                outstanding FX deal taking value.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Purchases</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays the total amount of FX deal purchases taking
                value on the displayed date.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Sales</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays the total amount of FX deal sales taking value
                on the displayed date.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Net Position</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays the net amount of FX deal purchases and sales
                on the displayed date.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>

      <tip>
        <para role="TEXT">: The result is sorted by value date in ascending order, which
        cannot be modified.</para>
      </tip>
    </section>

    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Deal Activity</title>

      <para role="TEXT">While performing inquiries on a specific net position by day, all
      underlying FX transactions that add up to the position are displayed,
      filtered by the position selected.</para>

      <para role="TEXT"><emphasis>Activity</emphasis> section contains the following
      details.</para>

      <informaltable frame="all">
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="column-1" colwidth="2668*" />

          <colspec colname="column-2" colwidth="6080*" />

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Field</entry>

              <entry>Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Net Indicator</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Allows you to select specific deals for net
                settlement.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Available for Net</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Indicates whether the deal is available for
                netting.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Deal Number</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays the deal number of the FX transaction.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Sequence</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Indicates a sequential number that identifies the FX
                deal.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Description</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays the description of the FX deal.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Currency Net Deal No</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays the netted deal number for a settled
                deal.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Counter Net Deal No</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Identifies the CTRCCY net settlement transaction deal
                number if the deal counter currency was netted.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Currency</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Indicates the currency in which the customer has an
                outstanding FX deal.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Amount</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays the amount of currency purchased or sold for
                the FX deal.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Counter Currency</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Identifies the counter currency in which the customer
                has an outstanding FX deal.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Deal Date</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Indicates the date the deal is entered.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">
                  <guilabel>Instruction Status</guilabel>
                </para>
              </entry>

              <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <para role="TEXT">Displays the status of payment instructions for the
                deal. This value can be either <emphasis>Complete</emphasis>
                or <emphasis>Incomplete</emphasis>.</para>
              </entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>

      <note>
        <para role="TEXT">: For the list of transaction details, you can filter and/or
        sort the results returned from the portal on a single or multi-column
        basis. Also, you can show or hide one or more columns as
        required.</para>
      </note>
    </section>
  </section>
</chapter>
